      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TILLY DUNNAGE NZ (8) is a newcomer to the Chantal Turpin yard from NZ. Has not raced for three months but looks forward enough after winning a recent trial. Can settle just behind them and wait on the sprint lane. Can kick off in Queensland with a win. MISS MUNCH (3) turned in a strong effort last start when she scored by a head at Redcliffe. Will enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Could work through her grades. TONJAY (4) came from this barrier and got home by 2.4 metres at Redcliffe on debut and has been back to the trials since. Strips fitter and could go on with the job. PICCOLO DIAVOLO (6) is ticking along well having finished runner-up in two Redcliffe outings off a spell, missing narrowly last time out.",
